I'm working on putting a 15 gal tank in my bus and have this problem as well.

When you say tar paper is this like the felt used on house roofs or is it more like the asphalt
based sound damping matieral that is used on the rear bulkhead over the engine compartment?

I have some of the asphalt based stuff. It is similar to Dynamat and I got it at McMaster Carr after
I read a thread about sound damping in the archives. I thought of using this stuff but I was afraid
that it might compress too much over time and cause the tank to become loose and shift around (not
good!).

